Iowa.

724
00:35:30,833 --> 00:35:32,267
[Applause]

725
00:35:32,300 --> 00:35:33,933
There must be
some mistake, Stuart.

726
00:35:33,967 --> 00:35:35,800
You can't be
Mrs. Carl hesby,

727
00:35:35,833 --> 00:35:37,367
can you?

728
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:40,067
And the name
submitted by
Mrs. Hesby,

729
00:35:40,100 --> 00:35:43,000
the name of the ajax
white knight,

730
00:35:43,033 --> 00:35:45,367
is sir Lancelot.

731
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:47,800
Sir Lancelot?

732
00:35:47,833 --> 00:35:50,100
That is
a better name.

733
00:35:50,133 --> 00:35:52,567
Ha ha ha!

734
00:35:52,600 --> 00:35:55,033
Your family
must be very proud.

735
00:35:55,067 --> 00:35:58,200
Ha ha ha!

736
00:35:58,233 --> 00:36:00,200
Sir cleanalot!

737
00:36:00,233 --> 00:36:01,700
Ha ha ha!

738
00:36:01,733 --> 00:36:03,900
Ha ha ha!

739
00:36:03,933 --> 00:36:05,400
Jodie is a liar.

740
00:36:05,433 --> 00:36:07,233
Either that
or she's just crazy

741
00:36:07,267 --> 00:36:08,933
or both.

742
00:36:10,667 --> 00:36:13,200
I mean, the idea
of Jodie

743
00:36:13,233 --> 00:36:15,600
being in charge
of anything...

744
00:36:15,633 --> 00:36:17,133
Just because she
went shopping

745
00:36:17,167 --> 00:36:18,633
for aunt Paula
a couple
of times.

746
00:36:18,667 --> 00:36:20,100
I took care
of her car.

747
00:36:20,133 --> 00:36:22,167
Good point.

748
00:36:22,200 --> 00:36:23,667
What's the problem

749
00:36:23,700 --> 00:36:25,167
with aunt Paula's
neighbor?

750
00:36:25,200 --> 00:36:26,667
Why can't we
sell her house?

751
00:36:26,700 --> 00:36:28,200
Because the guy's
a jerk.

752
00:36:28,233 --> 00:36:29,833
Part of
aunt Paula's house

753
00:36:29,867 --> 00:36:31,433
slops onto
his property,

754
00:36:31,467 --> 00:36:33,400
so we got to pay
an easement.

755
00:36:33,433 --> 00:36:35,400
What's an easement?

756
00:36:35,433 --> 00:36:37,900
An easement is...

757
00:36:37,933 --> 00:36:41,033
Money that you
got to pay a guy

758
00:36:41,067 --> 00:36:43,900
when your house
slops onto his
property.

759
00:36:43,933 --> 00:36:45,733
Jodie went over

760
00:36:45,767 --> 00:36:47,300
to negotiate
with him,

761
00:36:47,333 --> 00:36:48,800
and like an idiot,

762
00:36:48,833 --> 00:36:50,967
she offers him
$3,000--

763
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:53,333
3,000 for a little
easement.

764
00:36:53,367 --> 00:36:56,700
When dad heard this,
he flipped out.

765
00:36:59,733 --> 00:37:01,733
Your shot.

766
00:37:01,767 --> 00:37:03,667
I shoot
the stripey ones?

767
00:37:03,700 --> 00:37:05,933
Yeah,
the stripey ones.

768
00:37:05,967 --> 00:37:07,967
Anyway, I got
this lawyer

769
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:09,500
to handle it.

770
00:37:09,533 --> 00:37:10,967
That's not
working out,

771
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:12,900
and Jodie doesn't
trust me and dad
anymore.

772
00:37:12,933 --> 00:37:14,800
You got to talk
to this guy
tomorrow.

773
00:37:14,833 --> 00:37:17,567
I have to?

774
00:37:17,600 --> 00:37:19,800
You got to try
and chisel him
down a little.

775
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:22,467
Beer.

776
00:37:22,500 --> 00:37:24,200
Donnie, how
are you doing?

777
00:37:26,600 --> 00:37:28,267
That
your brother?

778
00:37:30,067 --> 00:37:31,667
