01:21:44,733 --> 01:21:46,200
Aah!

1834
01:21:46,233 --> 01:21:47,800
Cheese!

1835
01:21:51,433 --> 01:21:53,300
The doctors
in the emergency room

1836
01:21:53,333 --> 01:21:54,767
said if I wasn't so fat,

1837
01:21:54,800 --> 01:21:56,333
I would have really
gotten hurt.

1838
01:21:56,367 --> 01:21:57,667
The weird thing is,

1839
01:21:57,700 --> 01:21:59,167
we've never talked
about it since.

1840
01:21:59,200 --> 01:22:00,967
In fact,
I think that's when

1841
01:22:01,000 --> 01:22:03,967
the no-talk rule
began in our house,

1842
01:22:04,000 --> 01:22:06,033
but at 10 A.M. tomorrow,

1843
01:22:06,067 --> 01:22:08,100
all that will change.

1844
01:22:08,133 --> 01:22:09,600
This guy's
a good lawyer?

1845
01:22:09,633 --> 01:22:11,100
Yeah.

1846
01:22:11,133 --> 01:22:13,033
Says he can keep me
out of jail, huh?

1847
01:22:13,067 --> 01:22:15,300
Yeah. If you do
what he says, yeah.

1848
01:22:25,300 --> 01:22:26,633
Mr. Smalley.

1849
01:22:26,667 --> 01:22:28,133
Your family
has asked me

1850
01:22:28,167 --> 01:22:29,533
to help them

1851
01:22:29,567 --> 01:22:31,533
because
of some concerns
they have about you.

1852
01:22:31,567 --> 01:22:33,033
They have
some things

1853
01:22:33,067 --> 01:22:35,033
that they'd like
to say to you,

1854
01:22:35,067 --> 01:22:37,033
and I'm going to
ask you

1855
01:22:37,067 --> 01:22:39,067
just to sit
and listen,

1856
01:22:39,100 --> 01:22:40,867
hear them out,
and then--

1857
01:22:40,900 --> 01:22:42,533
then we'll give you
a chance to talk.

1858
01:22:42,567 --> 01:22:44,033
Can you agree
to that?

1859
01:22:44,067 --> 01:22:45,533
Who the hell are you?

1860
01:22:45,567 --> 01:22:48,033
Mr. Smalley, I can
understand this is
real uncomfortable--

1861
01:22:48,067 --> 01:22:49,533
who did this?

1862
01:22:49,567 --> 01:22:51,033
Oh, oh. You, huh?

1863
01:22:51,067 --> 01:22:52,367
Uh, Mr. Smalley,

1864
01:22:52,400 --> 01:22:53,700
your whole family
is concerned.

1865
01:22:53,733 --> 01:22:55,033
You know
about this guy?

1866
01:22:55,067 --> 01:22:58,033
I hope somebody
has told you
the whole story.

1867
01:22:58,067 --> 01:23:00,833
Why don't you just
sit down right here, hmm?

1868
01:23:02,133 --> 01:23:03,833
That's right.

1869
01:23:05,133 --> 01:23:06,667
Jodie,

1870
01:23:06,700 --> 01:23:08,833
you have something
to say to your father?

1871
01:23:16,067 --> 01:23:19,433
You were drunk
at all my weddings.

1872
01:23:19,467 --> 01:23:21,533
[Jodie sobbing]

1873
01:23:21,567 --> 01:23:24,033
Did you get to meet
her ex-husbands?

1874
01:23:24,067 --> 01:23:27,033
Dopey, drunky,
and shithead.

1875
01:23:27,067 --> 01:23:28,533
[Man]
You agreed to listen.

1876
01:23:28,567 --> 01:23:30,033
I didn't agree
to anything.

1877
01:23:30,067 --> 01:23:32,033
At least I stayed
with my ungrateful family

1878
01:23:32,067 --> 01:23:34,033
and provided for you.

1879
01:23:34,067 --> 01:23:36,533
None of you went hungry.

1880
01:23:36,567 --> 01:23:38,733
That's painfully obvious.

1881
01:23:38,767 --> 01:23:40,400
[Man]
Mr. Smalley.

1882
01:23:40,433 --> 01:23:42,767
A man might stay with you
if you weren't so damn fat.

1883
01:23:42,800 --> 01:23:43,900
Jesus!

1884
01:23:43,933 --> 01:23:45,900
What? I'm
under attack here.

1885
01:23:45,933 --> 01:23:47,733
It wasn't my fault.

1886
01:23:47,767 --> 01:23:49,067
You're an asshole!

1887
01:23:49,100 --> 01:23:50,833
Well, you want
a piece of me?

1888
01:23:50,867 --> 01:23:51,833
Yeah.

1889
01:23:51,867 --> 01:23:53,433
Come on!

1890
01:23:53,467 --> 01:23:55,033
Mr. Smalley, please.

1891
01:23:55,067 --> 01:23:56,600
Ha ha ha!

1892
01:23:56,633 --> 01:23:58,533
Unbelievable.

1893
01:23:58,567 --> 01:24:00,333
Sit down...Please.

1894
01:24:07,133 --> 01:24:08,533
Stuart,

1895
01:24:08,567 --> 01:24:10,333
do you have
something to say?

1896
01:24:12,567 --> 01:24:14,533
Dad...

1897
01:24:14,567 --> 01:24:16,033
There were a lot
of instances

1898
01:24:16,067 --> 01:24:17,533
in my childhood

1899
01:24:17,567 --> 01:24:20,100
when your drinking
made me feel bad,

1900
01:24:20,133 --> 01:24:21,700
but this is now,

1901
01:24:21,733 --> 01:24:24,033
and I want to talk
about now.

1902
01:24:24,067 --> 01:24:26,033
I have changed a lot

1903
01:24:26,067 --> 01:24:28,033
in the last
three years.

1904
01:24:28,067 --> 01:24:33,033
I mean, I lost
127 pounds,

1905
01:24:33,067 --> 01:24:34,533
and...

1906
01:24:34,567 --> 01:24:36,967
I don't think
you even noticed.

1907
01:24:37,000 --> 01:24:39,267
But more than that,

1908
01:24:39,300 --> 01:24:41,767
I've made a lot
of progress
as a person...

1909
01:24:43,067 --> 01:24:45,033
And it hurts me...

1910
01:24:45,067 --> 01:24:46,533
That...

1911
01:24:46,567 --> 01:24:48,033
[Sigh]

1912
01:24:48,067 --> 01:24:49,533
You refuse to--

1913
01:24:49,567 --> 01:24:51,900
to even see that.

1914
01:24:51,933 --> 01:24:56,533
Aw, it's o.K.,
Stuart.

1915
01:24:56,567 --> 01:24:58,533
I'm here for you.

1916
01:24:58,567 --> 01:25:00,100
Come on.

1917
01:25:00,133 --> 01:25:03,500
Why don't you give
your alcoholic dad
a big hug?

1918
01:25:03,533 --> 01:25:05,333
[Man]
Mr. Smalley.

1919
01:25:05,367 --> 01:25:06,833
Well, isn't that
what you do

1920
01:25:06,867 --> 01:25:08,333
in your 12-step
programs?

1921
01:25:08,367 --> 01:25:09,833
I always think

1922
01:25:09,867 --> 01:25:11,433
I should organize
one of these for you!

1923
01:25:11,467 --> 01:25:13,367
Because you're addicted.

1924
01:25:13,400 --> 01:25:15,033
You're addicted...

1925
01:25:15,067 --> 01:25:17,033
To 12-step programs!

1926
01:25:17,067 --> 01:25:18,533
Ha ha ha!

1927
01:25:18,567 --> 01:25:20,033
God, you'd drink, too,

1928
01:25:20,067 --> 01:25:22,800
if you had liberace
for a son.

1929
01:25:22,833 --> 01:25:24,033
Dad!

1930
01:25:24,067 --> 01:25:26,033
We're both drunks!

1931
01:25:26,067 --> 01:25:28,533
And you know what?
You're dangerous!

1932
01:25:28,567 --> 01:25:30,667
The alcohol has made you
dangerous

1933
01:25:30,700 --> 01:25:32,533
to yourself
and to all of US!

1934
01:25:32,567 --> 01:25:34,067
You've scarred
all of US!

1935
01:25:34,100 --> 01:25:35,533
I mean, look at me!

1936
01:25:35,567 --> 01:25:37,067
I haven't done shit
with my life!

1937
01:25:37,100 --> 01:25:38,733
And that's all my fault?

1938
01:25:38,767 --> 01:25:40,700
No, it's not
all your fault,

1939
01:25:40,733 --> 01:25:42,700
but stuff happened...

1940
01:25:42,733 --> 01:25:44,767
That made it hard.

1941
01:25:46,567 --> 01:25:48,933
You remember
my first year at Kennedy?

1942
01:25:48,967 --> 01:25:51,600
New school,
new kids.

1943
01:25:51,633 --> 01:25:54,533
You know, I actually
got up the courage

1944
01:25:54,567 --> 01:25:56,033
to have a party.

1945
01:25:56,067 --> 01:25:58,033
Remember?
Down in the basement?

1946
01:25:58,067 --> 01:26:00,333
We were playing
records and stuff.

1947
01:26:01,633 --> 01:26:03,600
And you got so drunk,

1948
01:26:03,633 --> 01:26:06,400
you fell down the stairs
in front of everybody.

1949
01:26:11,567 --> 01:26:13,033
That just--

1950
01:26:13,067 --> 01:26:15,400
that just
never happened.

1951
01:26:15,433 --> 01:26:17,267
Huh!

1952
01:26:21,067 --> 01:26:22,400
Mrs. Smalley?

1953
01:26:26,567 --> 01:26:29,267
Maybe if you just
cut down a little...

1954
01:26:31,067 --> 01:26:33,267
After the holidays.

1955
01:26:40,067 --> 01:26:41,600
Jesus.

1956
01:26:41,633 --> 01:26:43,400
Why did we do this?

1957
01:26:45,567 --> 01:26:49,033
There is one more
piece of information,

1958
01:26:49,067 --> 01:26:51,267
Mr. Smalley.

1959
01:26:53,067 --> 01:26:54,533
This is a letter

1960
01:26:54,567 --> 01:26:57,033
from the district attorney
of hennepin county

1961
01:26:57,067 --> 01:27:00,600
regarding your
hunting accident.

1962
01:27:00,633 --> 01:27:03,933
It says if you don't
get help...

1963
01:27:04,833 --> 01:27:06,567
You go to jail.

1964
01:27:09,133 --> 01:27:11,100
Hmm. Oh.

1965
01:27:11,133 --> 01:27:14,533
If this is what
it's like in rehab,

1966
01:27:14,567 --> 01:27:17,267
send me to jail.

1967
01:27:19,067 --> 01:27:21,767
I'll talk to you
at home.

1968
01:27:34,567 --> 01:27:36,767
Well, that was fun.

1969
01:27:38,067 --> 01:27:39,933
[Sigh]

1970
01:27:42,933 --> 01:27:45,400
That night,
I had this dream.

1971
01:27:45,433 --> 01:27:49,133
It's a recurring dream
I've had most of my life.

1972
01:28:18,900 --> 01:28:22,033
I'm holding dad in my arms,
and he looks up at me.

1973
01:28:22,067 --> 01:28:24,167
His eyes just look into mine

1974
01:28:24,200 --> 01:28:26,033
and seem to say,

1975
01:28:26,067 --> 01:28:27,533
"I'm sorry I'm so helpless.

1976
01:28:27,567 --> 01:28:29,733
"Thank you for saving me.

1977
01:28:29,767 --> 01:28:31,700
I love you."

1978
01:28:35,067 --> 01:28:38,500
And that's the end.

1979
01:28:40,633 --> 01:28:42,600
I can't take this.

1980
01:28:42,633 --> 01:28:44,100
You see, the thing is,

1981
01:28:44,133 --> 01:28:45,800
I have nothing
to spend it on.

1982
01:28:45,833 --> 01:28:48,100
You could spend it
on yourself.

1983
01:28:48,133 --> 01:28:50,600
No, I can't. Actually,
that's one of my problems.

1984
01:28:50,633 --> 01:28:53,333
I'm an anorexic spender.

1985
01:28:53,367 --> 01:28:55,100
I'll pay you back.

1986
01:28:55,133 --> 01:28:56,833
Whenever.

1987
01:28:58,133 --> 01:29:00,700
They called your bus.

1988
01:29:02,200 --> 01:29:03,667
Um...

1989
01:29:03,700 --> 01:29:07,667
I don't think
I'm coming back
for Christmas.

1990
01:29:07,700 --> 01:29:10,633
I have to get on
with my life.

1991
01:29:10,667 --> 01:29:12,600
Yeah.

1992
01:29:12,633 --> 01:29:14,600
It's going to be weird
not being home.

1993
01:29:14,633 --> 01:29:17,100
I'll miss the, uh...

1994
01:29:17,133 --> 01:29:18,767
Fighting, mainly.

1995
01:29:18,800 --> 01:29:20,300
Yeah.

1996
01:29:20,333 --> 01:29:22,933
You guys going to
be o.K.?

1997
01:29:24,500 --> 01:29:26,333
[Loudspeaker]
Final call.

1998
01:29:27,633 --> 01:29:29,600
Uh, take care of Kyle

1999
01:29:29,633 --> 01:29:31,100
and yourself.

2000
01:29:31,133 --> 01:29:33,033
You, too.

2001
01:29:39,400 --> 01:29:41,600
Go to meetings.

2002
01:29:43,100 --> 01:29:45,433
You know where I am.

2003
01:29:55,300 --> 01:29:57,067
And get a sponsor.

2004
01:30:04,500 --> 01:30:07,967
And the whole thing was
just a humongous disaster,

2005
01:30:08,000 --> 01:30:10,533
and mom and dad
won't talk to me,

2006
01:30:10,567 --> 01:30:12,400
and I told Jodie and Donnie

2007
01:30:12,433 --> 01:30:14,900
that I just--
I won't be coming back,

2008
01:30:14,933 --> 01:30:17,967
which means I'll be
having Christmas

2009
01:30:18,000 --> 01:30:21,533
without my family
for the first time ever,

2010
01:30:21,567 --> 01:30:23,533
and that's o.K.

2011
01:30:23,567 --> 01:30:25,600
Because I have
lots of friends,

2012
01:30:25,633 --> 01:30:27,533
and believe me,

2013
01:30:27,567 --> 01:30:29,533
we're going to celebrate

2014
01:30:29,567 --> 01:30:31,533
because when it comes
to partying,

2015
01:30:31,567 --> 01:30:33,533
no one gets down

2016
01:30:33,567 --> 01:30:35,233
like people in recovery.

2017
01:30:35,267 --> 01:30:37,267
It's true.

2018
01:30:38,433 --> 01:30:40,400
But still I know
it's going to be

2019
01:30:40,433 --> 01:30:42,467
a bumpy time for me
emotionally,

2020
01:30:42,500 --> 01:30:43,967
and that's o.K.

2021
01:30:44,000 --> 01:30:45,800
I have to accept that

2022
01:30:45,833 --> 01:30:48,900
because
as we say in program,

2023
01:30:48,933 --> 01:30:51,933
"alcoholism is
a threefold disease--

2024
01:30:51,967 --> 01:30:54,533
Thanksgiving, Christmas,
and new year's."

2025
01:30:54,567 --> 01:30:56,267
Isn't that clever?

2026
01:30:57,567 --> 01:31:01,100
Anyway, I guess I've finally
given up the fantasy

2027
01:31:01,133 --> 01:31:05,600
of the smalleys ever having
a Norman Rockwell Christmas--

2028
01:31:05,633 --> 01:31:09,600
or a Norman Rockwell anything,
for that matter--

2029
01:31:09,633 --> 01:31:12,033
and that's progress,

2030
01:31:12,067 --> 01:31:13,767
I guess.

2031
01:31:15,067 --> 01:31:17,033
And as we say,

2032
01:31:17,067 --> 01:31:18,533
"progress,

2033
01:31:18,567 --> 01:31:20,300
not perfection."

2034
01:31:23,967 --> 01:31:25,033
So...

2035
01:31:25,067 --> 01:31:27,033
Merry Christmas

2036
01:31:27,067 --> 01:31:29,033
and always remember

2037
01:31:29,067 --> 01:31:31,033
you're good enough,

2038
01:31:31,067 --> 01:31:32,533
you're smart enough,

2039
01:31:32,567 --> 01:31:34,033
and doggone it,

2040
01:31:34,067 --> 01:31:36,033
people like you.

2041
01:31:36,067 --> 01:31:38,033
[Man]
Clear.

2042
01:31:38,067 --> 01:31:39,533
O.k.!

2043
01:31:39,567 --> 01:31:41,033
Let's party!

2044
01:31:41,067 --> 01:31:42,533
[Cheering and applause]

2045
01:31:42,567 --> 01:31:44,267
[Music playing]

2046
01:31:45,567 --> 01:31:47,033
Merry Christmas,
Stuart.

2047
01:31:47,067 --> 01:31:49,267
Merry Christmas,
Stuart.

2048
01:31:51,567 --> 01:31:53,033
Jerry! Thank you
for coming.

2049
01:31:53,067 --> 01:31:55,033
So moving.
Merry Christmas!

2050
01:31:55,067 --> 01:31:56,333
Mea.

2051
01:31:56,367 --> 01:31:57,700
Merry Christmas.

2052
01:31:57,733 --> 01:31:59,033
I think
you're great.

2053
01:31:59,067 --> 01:32:00,600
Oh, I love you, too.

2054
01:32:00,633 --> 01:32:02,100
I think you're
just great.

2055
01:32:02,133 --> 01:32:03,600
I know.

2056
01:32:03,633 --> 01:32:05,600
O.k. That--that's good.

2057
01:32:05,633 --> 01:32:07,600
O.k. Merry--
merry Christmas.

2058
01:32:07,633 --> 01:32:09,100
Oh, I'm sorry.

2059
01:32:09,133 --> 01:32:10,733
That's--
that's o.K.

2060
01:32:10,767 --> 01:32:12,767
You two! Ha ha!

2061
01:32:14,067 --> 01:32:16,033
Oh! You didn't put that
on plastic, did you?

2062
01:32:16,067 --> 01:32:17,533
Oh, no. Cash only.

2063
01:32:17,567 --> 01:32:20,367
Sorry to take
your inventory.
Congratulations!

2064
01:32:20,400 --> 01:32:22,267
Thank you.

2065
01:32:27,300 --> 01:32:29,533
Ah, can you
excuse me?

2066
01:32:29,567 --> 01:32:31,267
Sure.

2067
01:32:35,567 --> 01:32:37,033
That was a great show.

2068
01:32:37,067 --> 01:32:39,200
I'm so proud of you.

2069
01:32:40,567 --> 01:32:42,267
Thank you.

2070
01:32:43,567 --> 01:32:47,033
Um, about
Christmas dinner--

2071
01:32:47,067 --> 01:32:49,000
I'm going to have
to give you a rain check

2072
01:32:49,033 --> 01:32:51,767
because I'm going to Ohio.

2073
01:32:51,800 --> 01:32:54,533
I called my family,
and I've reconciled with,

2074
01:32:54,567 --> 01:32:56,433
well, pretty much
all of them.

2075
01:32:56,467 --> 01:32:58,033
That's amazing.

2076
01:32:58,067 --> 01:32:59,567
It's a miracle.

2077
01:32:59,600 --> 01:33:02,000
No. It's a joke.

2078
01:33:02,033 --> 01:33:04,433
Ha ha! Ha ha!

2079
01:33:04,467 --> 01:33:05,733
Oh...

2080
01:33:05,767 --> 01:33:07,867
We're going to have
a great Christmas.

2081
01:33:20,567 --> 01:33:22,867
The best ever.

2082
01:33:34,567 --> 01:33:37,633
Come on. I want you
to meet some of my friends.

2083
01:33:37,667 --> 01:33:39,367
O.k.

2084
01:33:42,067 --> 01:33:43,533
This is Julia.
She's my best friend.

2085
01:33:43,567 --> 01:33:45,033
This is my big brother.

2086
01:33:45,067 --> 01:33:46,533
Hi, Julie. Don.

2087
01:33:46,567 --> 01:33:48,567
Ha ha! Come on.
Let's meet everybody.

2088
01:33:48,600 --> 01:33:53,067
* grab your coat
and get your hat *

2089
01:33:53,100 --> 01:33:57,400
* leave your worries
on the doorstep *

2090
01:33:57,433 --> 01:34:01,467
* just direct your feet

2091
01:34:01,500 --> 01:34:05,467
* to the sunny side
of the street *

2092
01:34:05,500 --> 01:34:10,467
* can't you hear
that pitter-pat? *

2093
01:34:10,500 --> 01:34:14,400
* and that happy tune
is your step *

2094
01:34:14,433 --> 01:34:18,900
* life can be so sweet

2095
01:34:18,933 --> 01:34:21,900
* on the sunny side
of the street *

2096
01:34:21,933 --> 01:34:26,900
* I used to walk
in the shade *

2097
01:34:26,933 --> 01:34:31,400
* with all my blues on parade

2098
01:34:31,433 --> 01:34:35,900
* but I'm not afraid

2099
01:34:35,933 --> 01:34:39,900
* this rover crossed over

2100
01:34:39,933 --> 01:34:44,400
* if I never have a cent

